    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-22T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-22T12:00:00-05:00" n="450"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Sp1/32</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-22T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 23, 6.50 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>836. Department’s 718, October 20, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d450fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Spanish Government has of its own accord taken action
                    suggested by Department. Officers and crew of German submarine <hi rend="italic"
                        >B–23</hi> which entered Corunna in July have just been sent to Alcala de
                    Henares, a few miles from Madrid for internment. Submarine remains under Spanish
                    surveillance at Ferrol.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
